item.description:
Binary Search — &lt;= vs &lt; Boundary Conditions
The golden rule: Ask — &ldquo;Has this index been fully eliminated as a candidate?&rdquo;
Yes → skip it: use mid + 1 / mid - 1 No → keep it: use mid 1. The Two Styles of Binary Search Every binary search loop falls into one of two mental models. The choice of &lt;= vs &lt; follows directly from which model you pick.

The difference between these two boils down to how they handle uncertainty and predictability.
1. The Deterministic Model: &ldquo;Same In, Same Out&rdquo; A deterministic model is like a rigid mathematical formula. If you provide the same input, you are guaranteed to get the exact same output every single time. There is no room for randomness or &ldquo;maybe.&rdquo;
Logic: $y = f(x)$ Perspective: It assumes that the system is fully known and that there is only one correct answer for any given state.
